node.accessibility_caption: Photo by SportsCenter on August 07, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, people standing and text that says '25 201 2018 BACK TPIONS PAMELA AND JAVALE MCGEE BECOME THE FIRST MOTHER-SON OLD-MEDAL DUO IN OLYMPICS HISTORY'.

node.text:
Pamela McGee and her son, JaVale McGee, are the first mother and son to win gold medals in Olympic history.

Pamela was a member of the 1984 squad that defeated South Korea 85-55 to win gold at the Olympics. Thirty-seven years later, JaVale secured a gold medal at the Tokyo Games.
